Migration
    Lift and Shift SQL Server to a VM
        => Azure Migrate
    Migrate non-SQL objects to SQL Server or AzureSQL
        => use SQL Server Migration Assistant
    Migrate SQL Server object to SQL DB/Managed Instance
        Migrate and/or update SQL Server
            => use Database Migration Assistant (DMA)
        Compare workloads between resource source and target SQL Server
            => use Database Experimentation Assistant  (DEA)
        Migrate open source Database (MYSQL, PostgreSQL, MariaDB) to azure - offline or online
            => use Azure Database Migration Service (DMS)
                Minimum downtime which is good for large migration
                Can do online using premium tier
                    need to allow outbound 443
                    need to have 1434: UDP for SQL Server
                    enable TCP/IP protocol
                On your target DB, control your permission on server such as firewall or DB firewall
                It's depend on your source DB so you can choose DB migrate online or offline
    Migration
        Online
            Means you can use services from Azure
        Offline
            Means you have to setup a program on your computer PC and configure

    Post Migration Validation
        You need to have some test such as performance and correctness to make sure all the data imported correctly
        YOu need to be careful for version compatibility
            For example: AzureSQL and Azure Managed instanced always have the latest version
        You need to verify if there's any missing indices